.PP
The \fBMPSImageMedian\fP applies a median filter to an image\&. A median filter finds the median color value for each channel within a kernelDiameter x kernelDiameter window surrounding the pixel of interest\&. It is a common means of noise reduction and also as a smoothing filter with edge preserving qualities\&.
.PP
NOTE: The \fBMPSImageMedian\fP filter currently only supports images with <= 8 bits/channel\&. 
